================================================================
Web-Interface for Solaris-Servers to display Status-Information
================================================================

The Interface is based on minimalistic HTML5 with jQuery (Java-Script)

Tested on Solaris 11 Express, targeted for Open Indiana as well

Installing lighttpd & PHP5:
  sudo pkg install lighttpd
  sudo pkg install php-52 (or any newer version if available)

Bundled 'install' Directory:
  - smf-svc-lighttpd.xml
    service-descriptor for solaris SMF, see also:
      http://redmine.lighttpd.net/wiki/1/LighttpdOnSolaris
      http://blogs.oracle.com/mandy/entry/lighttpd_smf_troubles
	 	
  - lighttpd.conf
    SSL on Port 443 and enabled Fast-CGI for PHP5, see also:
      http://redmine.lighttpd.net/wiki/1/Docs:SSL
	
Configuring SolarStatus:
	see conf.ini.php, that's it.
	
Feedback appreciated: kai@meder.info

Screenshot: https://github.com/hotzen/SolarStatus/raw/master/screenshots/custom-filter.png
Download:   https://github.com/hotzen/SolarStatus/raw/master/dist/SolarStatus_0.3.zip

